Babban jami'in Majalisar Dinkin Duniya ya yi watsi da ziyarar Pakistan saboda matsalar jirgin sama
ISLAMABAD (AP) - Shugaban Majalisar Dinkin Duniya mai jiran gado ya sanar a ranar Lahadi cewa ya dakatar da ziyarar da ya shirya kai wa Pakistan "saboda wasu matsaloli na fasaha".
A watan da ya gabata ne aka zabi jami'in diflomasiyyar Turkiyya Volkan Bozkir a matsayin shugaban babban taron Majalisar Dinkin Duniya karo na 75, kuma an shirya zai isa birnin Islamabad a ranar Lahadi.
Amma a wani sako da ya wallafa a shafinsa na Twitter, ya ce ziyarar da zai kai babban birnin Pakistan za ta jira.
A martaninsa ga Bozkir, ministan harkokin wajen Pakistan Shah Mahmood Qureshi ya wallafa a shafinsa na Twitter cewa, "Ina fatan in yi maka maraba da zuwa Pakistan nan ba da jimawa ba don wata ziyara mai ma'ana da kuma amfani".
Kwana guda da ya gabata, Qureshi mai farin ciki, yayin da yake sanar da ziyarar, ya yi fatan zai tattauna batutuwa da dama tare da Bozkir, ciki har da Kashmir, wanda aka raba tsakanin Pakistan da Indiya da ke makwabtaka da ita kuma duka biyu sun yi ikirarin mallakarta.
Pakistan da Indiya sun gwabza yaki biyu daga cikin uku da suka yi kan yankin da ake takaddama a kansa tun bayan samun 'yancin kai daga Turawan Birtaniya a shekarar 1947.
Bangarorin biyu na yawan musayar wuta a Kashmir, lamarin da ke janyo asarar sojoji da fararen hula a bangarorin biyu.
Pakistan tana son Majalisar Dinkin Duniya ta taka rawar gani wajen warware matsalar Kashmir a karkashin kudurorinta ta hanyar barin mutanen da ke zaune a yankin Himalaya su yanke shawarar ko suna so su hade da Indiya, da Pakistan ko kuma sun fi son 'yancin kai.
